  "text": "Suppose the true number of model components is unknown, we arbitrarily set the number of the seed points at 8 in the running of the X-EM. To measure the performance of these four methods, we utilized four indices: false positive (FP), false negative (FN), true positive (TP), and true negative (TN). The total error rate was defined as FP + FN [CITATION_1] . Table 2 summarizes the results of these four methods, where the results of Method II-IV are obtained from [CITATION_2] . In addition, Table 3 summarizes the total error rates of the four methods. It can be seen that the X-EM algorithm outperforms the other three methods. Further, Fig. 7 shows the five groups formed by the X-EM algorithm, in which it is indeed that the genes with the similar patterns have been classified as a group together.",
